        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 20 at 2:46PM MDT by NWS Great Falls MT</headline>
        <description>At 245 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 9
miles southwest of Townsend, moving northeast at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Townsend, Toston, Silos, Radersburg, and Goose Bay.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
